msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:77-2
msgid ""
"Additionally, the contents of the Math Viewer are displayed visually on the "
"screen. As the expression is navigated, the current element or partial "
"expression is highlighted so a sighted teacher can easily tell what part of "
"the expression is being spoken."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:78-2
msgid ""
"When using a Braille display, the entire expression remains on the display "
"as you use the <strong>ARROW</strong> keys to navigate parts of the "
"expression. However, the cursor (dots 7 and 8) moves to the start of the "
"partial expression that gains focus. Pressing a cursor router over a term in "
"the expression will immediately move the focus to the specific location in "
"the expression."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:79-2
msgid ""
"To customize how JAWS reads as you navigate expressions in the Math Viewer, "
"press <strong>INSERT+6</strong> on the number row to open Settings Center, "
"press <strong>CTRL+SHIFT+D</strong> to load the default settings file, and "
"search for “Math” in the edit field to move directly to the <a "
"href=\"SettingsCenter.chm::/Math/Math_Group.htm\">Math group</a> in the tree "
"view. For example, the default for MathCAT Navigation verbosity is set to "
"Medium in JAWS. This allows speech users reviewing a math expression to hear "
"information about the current element within a math expression like "
"\"superscript,\" or \"root.\" For math expressions containing a table or "
"matrix, this setting also allows JAWS to announce column and row coordinates "
"while navigating."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:80-2
msgid "Selecting a Braille Math Code"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:81-2
msgid ""
"If a refreshable braille display is connected, JAWS shows math expressions "
"on the display using either Nemeth or Unified English Braille (UEB Math). To "
"switch between Nemeth or UEB Math for displaying math content in the Math "
"Viewer or Braille Math Editor, press <strong>INSERT+EQUALS</strong>. Focus "
"display users can also press RIGHT SHIFT+DOTS 1-2-3-4-5-6 on the display's "
"keyboard to switch the math braille code."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:82-2
msgid ""
"Since Nemeth and UEB Math are only available in English, make sure JAWS is "
"configured for one of the English contracted braille output modes by doing "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:84-3
msgid ""
"Press <strong>INSERT+6</strong> on the number row to open Settings Center."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:85-3
msgid ""
"To apply changes to all applications, press <strong>CTRL+SHIFT+D</strong> to "
"load the JAWS default settings. To apply changes to a specific application, "
"select it from the <strong>Applications</strong> combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:86-3
msgid "In the Search edit box, type “Translation” without the quotes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:87-3
msgid ""
"Press <strong>DOWN ARROW</strong> to move to Translation in the filtered "
"search results in the tree view and press <strong>ENTER</strong> to move "
"focus to the Translation group. Press <strong>RIGHT ARROW</strong> to expand "
"the group."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:88-3
msgid ""
"In the Language combo box, make sure English – United States is selected."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:89-3
msgid ""
"In the Output combo box, make sure one of the Grade 1 or Grade 2 options is "
"selected."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:90-3
msgid "Select OK to save your changes and close Settings Center."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CAccessing_Math_Content.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:92-2
msgid ""
"<strong>Tip:</strong> If using a Focus Braille display, you can press "
"<strong>DOTS 1-2-4-5-7-8 CHORD</strong> to quickly switch to contracted "
"braille."
msgstr ""

